<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A young man has died after falling out of his boat at a popular fishing spot on the New South Wales mid-north coast.</p>

<p>The fisherman, believed to be in his 20s, was discovered about four nautical miles off Diamond Head, south of Port Macquarie, on Wednesday afternoon.</p>

<p>His body was found by strangers on a nearby boat who hauled him out of the water and attempted to revive him. </p>

<p>The fisherman, believed to be in his 20s, was discovered about four nautical miles off Diamond Head, (pictured) south of Port Macquarie on Wednesday afternoon</p>

<p>They rushed him back to shore at the Crowdy Head boat ramp where they were met by volunteers from Marine Rescue New South Wales, reported the Daily Telegraph. </p>

<p>He died a short time later despite efforts to resuscitate him using a defibrillator and oxygen. </p>

<p>His four-and-a-half metre boat was found a short time later.</p>

<p>Police have seized the boat and will prepare a report for the coroner to determine the cause of death.</p>

<p>They will investigate whether the man suffered a medical episode.  </p>

<p>He is yet to be formally identified. </p>

<p>They rushed him back to shore at the Crowdy Head boat ramp where they were met by volunteers from Marine Rescue New South Wales (pictured)</p>
